      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds like a pretty solid argument for the debt side, but doesn't that basically prioritize the interests of lenders and banks over the actual well-being of citizens? Like, isn't it a bit \"reckless\" to let people suffer in poverty just to balance a ledger?",
